\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid13107468 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Where were you born and when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, I was born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} on 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day}{\xmlattrvalue 27}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1902}}}the twenty-seventh of November 1902
{\*\xmlclose}. I was the second - of a family of five girls. And we stayed in Denniston in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How much difference in age was there between you and your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 About two and a half years - between the first two, then three, then one - and a half, and then seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Haved you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Can you tell me how old he was when he died and when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Seventy-nine, almost eighty, in - 1949.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did he belong to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Originally no. Originally on the outskirts of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in - well, in a small village called Eaglestown. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That's Renfrewhire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. But as he lost his parents when he was very small, he was one of the youngest of quite a large family - the family w
ere separated for a time until they grew up. Because both parents died when father would be five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was he looked after by relatives then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. There were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Or did he have to go into a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, there - looked after by various connections, the family was all split up. Until they grew up, when they all got together again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So many families are split up and never find each other again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No, that was true. But - they had not only lost their parents but shortly after that the e
ldest sister died, which made it - that made it impossible for them all to keep together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of job did your father do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, he was - a House Factor and Insurance agent. First of all - with - a firm - in that same line and then - by the 
time he was in his early twenties started on his own. And I know - I know that he got married - in - 1899, and a year later his first daughter was - born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That was your eldest sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What exactly did a house factor have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I know what an agricultural factor does, was it similar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
No, he looked after property - that belonged to various people, he looked after the repairs, the - mainly outside repairs, or small things, not decoration inside, but all outside repairs were taken care of. All plumbing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It was the fabric of the building that he was concerned with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 All the - yes, all the - all the fabric - of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He wasn't just employed by one person then to look after that persons house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh n
o. Oh no, he was - looked after a number of peoples property. Actually one in particular but that owned a - a great deal. But also others and then latterly - quite a lot of property of his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He'd just collected it through it through the years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, but he also - was an insurance agent, and he was a surveyor. He was a Fellow of the Surveyors Institute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He carried on in the same job all the way through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He had his own business from his early twenties until the day he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He didn't retir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1138566\charrsid5124377 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
She came from a small village, not far from Eaglestown, Busby. Originally. But her father - was a weaver, and came to Glasgow - to open a mill in Bridgtown, near Denniston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So that's how they came to meet each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. And she was one of a fam - large - large family of daughters, no sons again, and - by the time - I knew them my grandparents stayed in Barr Head, not far from Glasgow either, where my grandfather had another mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So your mother wouldn't have to go out and work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
No. Oh, they had lots to do, because she was one of the youngest of that family. So there was always a baby to be looked after. You can understand, all the elder sisters - getting mar
ried, having their family, a girl growing up - just another pair of hands to look after a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Good experience for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. But she said from the age of twelve she always seemed to have a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were saying that she was keen on embroidery too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. Her - her father - I don't know if this is of interest, but - her father who was in weaving had a great sense of colour. His cousin was a painter and decorator - in Glasgow. Another - was - to do with - jewellery. So that there was a co
n - there was a connection and I know that - some of the - family - of these cousins went into art.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So it's gone all the way through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. One of my eldest - neph - my eldest cousins was an architect, and a very fine water colourist. Mother - mo
ther could do - three design - of her own for embroidery. She did a very little painting but - became so busy that she never had much time. Mm hm. But it - it was her paint box I began with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about where you stayed, did you always stay in the same house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
We stayed for a long time in - a flat. Fortunately - it was very open, because there was a bowling green in front, and a big field behind. We were all set to move - at the end of the first world war when mother took ill. So we remained where w
e were for a time, before we moved to a much roomier house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of size was the flat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 There were - four rooms and kitchen but you see the kitchen was very much a place where - you could play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It would be a living kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No, it was never that. But you were free to - do rather messy games - there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were lucky to have a mother who allowed you to do that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 My mother had the patience of Job and was superb with children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That was her vocation was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You say there were four rooms in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What were they, were they bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well - well, there was really - a very big bedroom that had two large beds in it. And then another bedroom that mother and
 father used. And a dining room and what was called a drawing room, but there was a big - bit off it that could be curtained. And it could act - it acted more as a large wardrobe - than anything else. But - we never - felt the lack of space because we - h
ad a house - that - had been built by my grandfather, at the coast. So that whenever - from springtime on, weekends were not spent in the city at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Whereabouts was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 At Upper Stelmerly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That's Ayrshire isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was it just your family that went there, or did your cousins and those families go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Origin - originally it was my grandfather. And - he and the cousins - of his that I mentioned earlier - built three villas. The bottom flats of which were let. The
 top flat, which was built to be entered separately - had - about six rooms - and kitchen, mainly bedrooms. Which were well and truly filled. And - and by the age of - ten or eleven my father had taken over that house. So that that was where you spent - y
our weekends, your short holidays, though we went further a field for our - long holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your mother have anybody to help her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. She always had - a maid who lived in the house. And then - someone would come - for - heavier cleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Like floor washing and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. And - as - it wasn't the day of washing machines. Washing was done in a wash house, and a woman came, for a whole day, to do that each week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was the wash house downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Down - no, actually you went - it was different to most flats. Up - we stayed up what they called one stair up, but half roads up that stair there was a landing, and a glass door which led out to the wash house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That is unusual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And someone came in to do the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You say you had someone to live in, did you stick to the same one or did they come and go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh one stayed when we were young for many years. Then there were various - ones that - didn't last as long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Didn't quite take the place of the one that had been there a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh no. She was a Highland girl - who - wouldn't have left but she left to be married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your mother train her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, but I think - being country, she came from Rosemarkey, up North - she - would be very well trained in the more ordinary things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ordinary housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did she have anything to do with you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Or did your mother look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, but - she - Maggie was - marvel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1138566\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 ous too with children, that's why I remember her so well. She too was patient with children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1138566\charrsid5124377 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 s things. But mother did all the baking. And all the sewing. And in these days - your clothes, except your - outdoor coats, were mainly maid at 
home. Because - ready made was - rather a nasty word. It really was. And - mother had - a Miss Munro who came for a week at a time, came each day for a week. And - mother did all the cutting, Miss Munro did all the machining, mother did the hand work. And
 - from an early age - we were taught to unpick hems, or to lay hems.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 These were bits and pieces that you could do when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. Uh huh. So that you learned quite a lot, the same with - cooking and baking. Which was done by mother in the main.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did she make bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
No. No, but she made oatcakes. And in my grandfather's day my grandfather called oatcake bread. He called bread loaf. Well - because my grandmother made oatcakes daily. Mother only made them - perhaps once a week. But they were done - in the big }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1138566\charrsid5124377 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
arrels, which were toasted on a grid in front of the kitchen fire, and one of the jobs - of young - youngsters, was to watch these curl, and see that they didn't burn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of cooking facilities did your mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
It was the old fashioned range, and above it - to the side - a gas - fitment. With - grill, and a couple of rings. On the other side of the range there was a hob that you could simmer things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You would keep a kettle on there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
 And a large - sort of - fork shaped thing that lay on top so that you could balance a big pot to bring it to the boil. Like soup. These things that perhaps were going to be on for a long time. Oh jam or course, these kind of things were all made at home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your mother make a lot of jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You had to buy fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, because we went out to my grandfather's and picked the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 gooseberries}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377  and blackcurrants. There again the children lent a hand with that. Managed to pick quite a lot in spite of what you swallowed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Green gooseberries aren't all that good for tummies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well I don't know, no - there were gooseberries for cooking, but there were also a lot of what were called sulphur gooseberr
ies, slightly yellow, very very sweet to eat. No sugar required there. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about pickles and things, did your mother go in for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 A bit. But not to the same extent as the - the jams. At a - a later stage - during the first world war I
 can remember - we - pickled eggs of course, in water}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
glass, we made certain preserves - to help to - eke out - in the fruit line - that weren't quite jams, but more of a mixture of fruit. For eat with pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did it have sugar in it to preserve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, a certain amount, though sometimes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It's not like bottling fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, not quite, no, I did plenty of that myself later. But that was during the last war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Your mother didn't bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Not - no, not a great deal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You say your mother made your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
These - we were fortunate in that, there was a very good shoemaker, and he made your shoes for you. You were fitted and they were made to measure and your - for the winter you
 had short boots, but they were made of fine kid, and - what they called glace kid, and - they were made to measure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That was a luxury wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. The only things I can remember that you bought that weren't specifically made for you were sli
ppers for dancing. For the dancing class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You didn't get those made for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you ever have to get them repaired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Oh yes, things were repaired. Nothing was wasted, things were well repaired. But there again, as I 
say, this was a proper - shoemaker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That would be quite something, going to get your feet measured for a new pair of shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, but you see - like the dressed, there weren't as many things made - for various fittings, as there are nowadays. Nothing like it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
d on clothes and shoes from one to the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh yes, most assuredly, in fact many a - shout was made about that, if you got something new - the younger ones saying, that'll be for me and that'll be for - somebody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 They quite looked forward to getting things then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
It didn't bother them. It didn't bother them at all. But since so many things were made at home - a lot didn't need to be passed on in that they were made with large hems or tucks, where you coul
d really wear them - pretty well out. I think we were rather sore on things. Very. We were very active, and we were fortunate in the activities we could have, because - it was one of the - earliest places to have a swimming baths - for one thing, within t
wo minutes of the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 We all went. Beginning at the age of about - six I think. But my father and mother were members to their last days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You went as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No. It was - the - men and women were separate, the
re were different times for them. But - the older people - could go for the Turkish bath and then the swim, until you were about fifteen, you were just allowed in the - sprays, and the baths. But it was very - it was very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You weren't allowed in the Turkish bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, but it was - very good for children you know. Because - you think on it. There were no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 immerses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 . And it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have a bathroom in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. An excellent bathroom, but - with five girls and two - three grown up
s counting a maid, though latterly as we got bigger the maid didn't live in, that's - I made a mistake there - but - as you - you - all got - a bath - or two - in the week, you then had three days at the baths, Monday, Thursday and Saturday where you coul
d go to the baths - and have a hot spray and a scrub and then your swim, which is a big help on hot water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Combining business and pleasure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. And thoroughly enjoyed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you learn to swim there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did someone teach you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. There was a baths master. Who taught you. And - if you weren't very quick your sisters flung you in, you - just had to learn to get there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You say that your father didn't help in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No. He was an excellent provider but left mother - to attend to - almost everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did he have long hours of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Very. Yes. Yes. He was - always out by about eight thirty. And very often, though he did come home at lunchtime, and of course in these days a midday dinner - 
was what was done - he came home sometimes at teatime, but he very often returned to the office and worked late, quite often 'til - about nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So you wouldn't really see a great deal of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, except holiday times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What about weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh yes. He was always there then. And he was - when we were - at the coast always ready to fit in - with the family. Whether it was golf or walking or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He enjoyed your company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Oh yes, but just - you see, his work took up a lot of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have any jobs to do regularly at home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
No. Except - to see that you left your room, bedroom - right. And every so often you would be told - I'm going to look at all the drawers tomorrow, so see that they're all tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So you had to have a blitz on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, yes. And - when you got older - you had great arguments as to what would go out and what would stay in. And sometimes your sisters wanted things you had and sometimes you wanted things they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You used to have a swap round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have to help with your younger sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. Not much, except that your - you watched them, - that field that I said was there, was most excellent because - little children could 
be quite safe once they were over this high paling, which went all round. And there were parts where little ones played, parts where bigger boys played cricket - or practiced their golf swing, you see, and - places where we used to make tents against the 
paling, and pretend you were - far far away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Very definitely. Eight o'clock, until you were - nearly fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you all go at the same time or was it graduated by age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Except the youngest, it wasn't graduated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Of course she was so much younger than the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. Yes. But I can remember that because - many of our holidays were spent in Ealey, in Fifeshire, where a curfew bell rang at eight o'clock. And no matter where you 
were, the idea was, to run as fast as you could - and get into your bed - preferably - well washed, brushed, before that bell stopped ringing. But you were allowed to get up as early as you liked in the morning. I remember one time wakening and thinking w
e would go for a swim, one of my sisters and I, and we were in the water and thought it very cold 'til we heard the same clock strike and realized it was 4 a.m. So - my recollection is that we went straight back to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You had to go to bed at eight o'clock even on holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You weren't allowed any latitude there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Well - if a mother had had five children, and she's been supervising them - on the beach a good bit of the time, and attending both to the - clothes - once again remember
 you didn't have a washing machine, and - the meals, and that they had been up early - her only free time was - when we were out the road. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you take your maid with you on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Until my youngest sister was five, we took a 
house, for a couple of months. But - after that we shortened that holiday and spent the rest of the time down at Stelmerley. But - by that time - my father felt that - the only way for mother to get a holiday was - to go to a hotel, that reminds me our mo
ther - the trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 ling was so different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How did you go, by train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
You had to go by train, but first of all there was a cab. Not a taxi. Remember there were no motors - to begin with. And - you went by cab, and you had first of all sent most of your luggage in advance, as it was too much to travel with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You would need quite a large vehicle for seven of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. So that your luggage in the main went ahead. A large - basket hamper, an immense thing, a large - black patent box and th
en various cases. Even the packing was a ritual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have to take your own linen and towels and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes, that too. And that - your waterproofs and your shoes, and any coats were what went in that big hamper. Then finger things - to t
he smaller - yes. And even large hat boxes because hats were worn more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have to wear a hat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Not on holiday except on - at the weekends. Then yes, definitely. And my recollection of the first world war was that it broke out when we were t
here. We had been there for July and - for August. Father said, we're just as well to stay there, things would be just as bad. But I do remember - that all that luggage I'm telling you about - was lost between Christchurch and Glasgow. And some of it turn
ed up about a month later. Some of it, mildewed, been lying in a siding. Because the traffic was just haywire. Because of the war. mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You wouldn't have thought it would have such immediate affect on the transport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, you see I think it was
 the - a matter of transport being redirected, because of the movement of troops. And then - because it was summer, a great many people were away from their normal homes, they had to get back, they had to get their names in for whatever company - they wer
e in, because many of them had been in OTC's in the school, and they went straight from school into the Army. Some of them - just - boys. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That would be rather a lost?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, well, most of the things did turn up, though in very bad conditi
on, but the said hat boxes never appeared again. That I remember, and one of the things I remember about trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
ling, was - you see there wasn't heating as such in the trains. There were - for wintertime - there was big long tins - that were filled with hot water - you put your feet on. That's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 In the middle of the carriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, that's - really - sort of - pre-world war one and during - that - world world war one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 When you were going to Skelmerley for the weekends how did you travel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Ah, yes, well - you see, you weren't all going together, by that time you were getting bigger, and those coming from - mother possibly went down with my youngest sister, and the rest who were wanting to go - went down by the four thirty train after school
. And you kept - you didn't need to - carry much because you kept clothes there. Old coats, Wellingtons, waterproofs etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 But you didn't have to go down unless you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, those who wanted to stay at home stayed because unless mother wa
s going for a time she didn't take the maid, the maid - looked after father. Well, you see, by the time we'd got older - the maid was coming daily. And - she attended to father, unless we were going for a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about meal times? Where did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Always the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You didn't have breakfast in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you all eat together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Mainly. Except if father's times didn't - fit. But otherwise we ate together - by the time - I was eleven I was then trave}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
ling to school, and - wasn't coming home in the middle of the day, and the others as they grew older, that followed. My eldest sister - for her preference, went to the local school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were allowed to have preferences in that sort of thing were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. I think so. I had got used to trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 ling. I had been in the habit of travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
ing on a Saturday morning into town anyway. So - before I had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was it a tram that you trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 led in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. And if you liked to walk home you could save a ha'penny. Which bought you four toffee balls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was it worth it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Well our mother always felt that if you wanted to do that at least the walk would have done you good, and you would have walked off the said toffee balls by the time you got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were you allowed to talk during mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. I - don't think anybody ever stopped us talking. We were stopped if we all - were all talking at once}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377  too much. But we were still in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 clined to do that - after we were grown up. My youngest sister had a record player - no - a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 A gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 phone?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, a tape recorder - which she had got for her own - speeches. And - put it on when we didn't know. We were all talking at once, shocking.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were you able to choose what you got to eat or was it put in front of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
No, you - had your meal put down. It might not be your taste, you had to try and take a little of it, but you were simply told - well - if it's not your choice this time it may be the next time, but nothing else was offered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You did without?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. So generally you ate most things. You weren't allowed too many likes and dislikes. Not possible with a large family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes, there was always lots of that. On the whole, plain food. But - very - good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Your mother was a good cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh very. Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was the choice of food geared to your father's likes and dislikes do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He had very few dislikes. I can only remember two - one was custard and the other was curds. Kenneth is exactly the same. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and to sit up properly at the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. But then - that had been learnt so young that it was taken for granted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You didn't have to be told about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, you were certainly told if you tried lounging - at table. Or - moving about in your seat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You weren't to fidget?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about reading at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Never. Never allowed. My father would never have dreamt of doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He didn't have the newspaper in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Not - only later and very often I was the one that was asked to read out - things to him, if there was something of great interest to him at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 When could you leave the table, could you leave as soon as you were finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
No. No. You waited 'til - at least 'til all the children were finished. If - father - was - later, perhaps later coming in - sometimes you see, but on the whole - you were not allowed to leave until ev
eryone was finished. Unless there was something special on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 If you were going to a class or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were saying that you got good plain food, did you have meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. And fish. As often as not. From an ear
ly age we stopped having cooked breakfast, but that was a matter of choice. You always had meat - that would be midday dinner. And you either had fish - or bacon and egg in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 A high tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. That was when the baking was for, in the main. Bought things except a loaf - were seldom in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You - did you have your own place at table that you always sat at, or did you sit anywhere you liked?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh anywhere you liked. Whoever was in first I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Who dished out the food, mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Mother. Father - did the carving. But - apart from that mother dished. You see, in those days - soup for instance was always brought in a tureen to the table. And was served from there. So that mother served that and she served the veg
etables, but - father - carved the meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did she serve you in any special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She didn't start with father and work down to the smallest child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I think - I - no, I don't think there was any special order because father would be
 - still cutting meat when mother was putting plates out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What about when your younger sisters were very young, when the littlest one was a baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Well you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Who fed her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh well, by then we all wanted to lend a hand. You see,
 I was twelve when she was born. I was twelve when she was born, my elder sister fourteen and a half, she was really looked on as our baby, more than mother's. And - I can recollect mother trying to - chastise her for something. I think she seldom did at 
any time. And - we all - got hold of her, mother, and - to stop her. And she laughed, she said - I've brought up four, why won't you let me bring up the fifth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about your maid, how did she eat, where did she eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 In the kitchen. Which was very comfortable I can assure you. We used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 After you were finished was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh no, at the same time as ourselves, in fact - now that you mention it I think - her plate was passed through first. I think I'm right in that. Yes. The only thing tha
t we drank there were like hot drinks like blackcurrant drinks, not Ribena, made with - with blackcurrant jam. Hot juicy drinks or - the eating of oranges. Juicy oranges.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was a thing made of birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh very much so. Everybody had to have something for the person whose birthday it was, no matter how little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you make the presents yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Sometimes, quite a lot. Oh sometimes - sewn things. All - sometimes bought. But we had all learnt from
 an early age to use our hands - in making things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And that was cheaper than buying things too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, for one thing there had always been - lots of scraps from the things that - the frocks - dresses that had been made, and to begin with you used many of these for your dolls clothes. And - that taught you very often how to put things together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about a birthday cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Not so much, no, very often it was - the old fashioned plum pudding, with the various - sixpences and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 pence and - the ring and button and - thimble in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You had that at dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you get parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Terrific parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Can you tell me about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Well - in the first place, my mother - liked people about
. Parties - were - for instance - you - family parties of course were Christmas - were New Year, mainly, at my grandfather's, and - at my mother's at Christmas. Our individual parties - throughout the year - were never given on birthdays. Never birthdays,
 
because mother objected to birthday presents from outsiders. She didn't think it was fair. That was for your family. So that a party was given and none of this bringing of presents. I carried the same thing when my daughter was small, and I can remember d
uring the last war, one of my sister's specifically writing on her invitations, no presents please. All the mothers round about thanked her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It gets to be a racket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. But - the parties - were - you've to remember that - it was before the - be
fore the day of vacuums as you know them, although we had - a family vacuum that went from - one house to another - during cleaning time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 For spring cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. It had a large nozzle, not unlike - the Electrolux, that was worked by a system o
f bellows that you had all to take turns of jumping on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That would be great fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
It was, but even youngsters legs can get tired on it. But when you were having a party - the whole room - was covered - by a large very heavy linen cloth, like heavy heavy damask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Would this come from grandfather's mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Very - well, very possibly. But that was a thing, not just our house. But if there were big parties, it was called a crumb cloth, for collecting all the crumbs and all the spills, from the lemonade, the - things, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 it was mostly not bottles but si}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
phons of lemonade, that you got. I can remember that. I can always remember - also remember that - we were very boisterous and for - all parties there was always the teatime and then the supper time.
 And - I think they consumed far more sweet things than the children do today. At the party time. At a party time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have a sit down meal for your parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Oh yes. There would be - perhaps about - thirty or more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And your mother would do all the catering for that herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Oh yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You did have the advantages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh, there isn't any doubt.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was your father an easy person to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Very. He didn't talk a great deal. He was fond of rea
ding, when he got time. He had a great many interests - and certainly encouraged anything that would broaden your education. He - belonged to a club - that was to encourage - singers, pianists, all the arts really, and - many of the top people - in singin
g - and music - and poetry - I heard there before they were well known.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of club was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
It was called the Talent Club. And - it encouraged all these people. Robert Wilson I heard when he was a young man with one of the most beautiful sweet voices I've ever heard. Kathleen Ferrier, I heard there. I heard a lecture by G.K. Chesterton himself.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did father take you to this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. There were social evenings, apart from the concert you see and you met people and - you had tea. And - y
ou - well I - I'm trying to think, I remember Yates reading his poetry. And ever so many authors who came and told us - really almost gave us their autobiography. Which was most interesting, and it certainly helped to widen your - field of interest.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your father make you go to these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh no, no, no, you were invited. If you wanted. That was as you were beginning to grow up. But when I was younger - I had gone to elocution where - I got an interest - in Shakespeare, Dickens, various other author
s, that augmented by school education. In a way that I didn't quite realize until later, when I began to sit exams and realize how much I knew about certain - books and plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You had more background information than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. And of cour
se you were - taught - quite a lot - about the various authors as well as reading their work. It gave - it did widen - it did widen your - your interests.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was your father musical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Not of himself. But very keen to take you. Mainly light operas. W
e were taken of course to begin with to Gilbert and Sullivan. He had heard the very first performance of the Mikado. In - in Scotland. And - as a young boy - he - before he was in business for himself - he collected, because of his interest in the theatre
 his boss gave him tickets and let him collect the rents from various theatres in Glasgow, which let him attend the performances you see, and at that time he wouldn't have much money.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 But it would be a real perk for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. And - in fact 
as a young boy he had his own - little - theatre that you made. You know? And - yes, well that was where they got the name - penny plain and tuppence coloured, for the books from which these characters were cut. For the plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You went to the theatre fairly often then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh yes, fairly often, though - not when we were very young. No, you attended the pantomime and you attended the - Handler's Circus which was - quite a - thing in Glasgow, a large circular stage, and after all the turns were on the 
ends was always a great water scene. And that - was the highlight of the evening, as we insisted on having the front seats where you had to be covered with water - keep the water - we weren't happy unless we had got splashed a bit. But later, by the time 
you got into your teens - you attended - quite a lot - both stage - drama productions and - and musical. But we were lucky in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you all go together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Very often. Yes. Very often. There again - those who wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You seem to have been allowed a fair bit of choice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh lots of freedom. Lots of freedom. Very few restrictions. My mother alway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 
s said - never have too many noes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377  to children, but be sure if you promise them anything - even a spanking, that they get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She would have done very well nowadays wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Oh excellently. She was a marve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 lous teacher. Had lots of patience to show you how to do anything. And when we were grown up many children came to the house saying they wanted to see my young sister but they would stay with mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She was this good with children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh excellent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would be when you grew up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Reliable. Kindly. Thoughtful of others, and not thinking yourself too important. I would say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did they sort of stress the way that you behaved towards your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, I would say so. Though it didn't always work out. There was lots of arguments, there always are you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did they ever come to blows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh - only occasionally, but - they did - lots of noisy rows. But they never lasted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your mother interfere when you were having a row like that or did she let you get on with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She left you and then - would always insist that the quarrel was made up before you went to your bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What about children apart from your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh the house had always lots of other children, we rarely sat down to a meal without just our own family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Had mother any restrictions on the children that came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, so long as - so long as they behaved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You could choose your own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you tend to choose children your own age to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I think on the whole you did you see - that was where I think we were very fo
rtunate. All round about us were families about the same size as ourselves perhaps three, perhaps four, but - in nearly every family there was one to fit your own age group. And - I could - mention a dozen families that that is true of. In fact my younges
t sister, some years ago, they had - a dinner party in town to collect all the ones of her age group, from that circle, many of them are very well known people now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were they all sort of the same background as yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 More or less. More or les
s. Different businesses of course, but more or less. And they - at - attended the little school beside us to begin with, they travelled in to town together later. They had gone to the baths. There was a local - tennis court - within a - stone's throw more
 or less, the fathers of the same people played bowling - played bowls - across the road from us, and then they attended - the same churches, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What did your parents think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Never. I never heard my father or mother swear in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What would have happened if one of you children had come out with a word?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
I think most assuredly you would have been rushed from the room and into your bedroom. Any rows were never - never took place in public. Always - if - there was any scolding - it was in your own bedroom, never in front of your - the rest of the family.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was it usually just a scolding that you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ah, except after the tiny stage. It's - except after the tiny stage. But then bad behaviour - was never permitted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Just a word was enough was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. I would say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What was the position if grown ups were there and were talking, were you allowed to join in or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Not if it was interrupting the grown ups. If they - talked to you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You could join in a conversation with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Oh yes. But no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It wasn't a case of be seen and not heard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, I think that was a little more so in my grandfather's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Slightly more old fashioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or from one more than the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, from both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Although you didn't see your father so much as your mother he had quite an influence on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh without doubt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you get presents at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. You always - the - the usual Santa Claus thing of hanging up the stockings and when you got older you were ones that hung up and filled the stockings. Yes. When you - yes, when you were older. But
 there was always apart from that a present from your father - from your mother. Father always gave us money. And he always said, I really hadn't time, but he knew perfectly well that we were all very anxious to get the money, it was quite possibly books 
for the other presents you had been given. Oh yes, you depended on it, and - and you see - by the time you were a little - oh, getting into your teens he was very generous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Probably it was better, you would be able to buy something that you really wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes, but quite often you had it - part of it - sort of booked for the various things you were giving your sisters etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about Christmas Day, were you together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Christmas Day -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Or did you have visitors in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Ah yes, you would have visitors in but generally you went to the church service on Christmas morning, while mother - saw to it that the dinner which would be - the Christmas meal was got ready. It would be rather later than ordinary lunch. Later i
t became a proper dinner, once you were grown up and then it was later in the day. But - the - Christmas - there would generally be some aunts or uncles and - or cousins would join you - for Christmas Day. But - at that time, in the main - it was New Year
s
 Day that was held and it wad held at my grandfather's house, which fortunately was very large because so was the family. Because my mother had been one of seven, and - by the time all their families arrived - for New Years Day dinner - yes, I think there
 would - well, one - had only one. Three apart from that was the smallest number.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did they feed the children first and then the adults?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No. They - no, they all sat but - there was a very large dining table for all the adults, and - and - the
 eldest of the cousins, and a large round table - for all - the - smaller fry, and you graduated from that to the bigger table as we got on, but our family happened to be - among the youngest. So - it - it was - I never got there. I never got to the bigge
st table. But it was fortunate and I may tell you it was a pretty roomy house and it's now a community centre, well as one cousin said, it always was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh well, at the party everybody had to do a turn. Whether it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It would be quite a long programme then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, but - no matter what, everybody had to do something. Sometimes - a family, one or two of them - who were good singers, our family weren't on the whole - though some of them are fairly musical - b
ut some of the other cousins were particularly good singers, and I can remember one family who sang quite a bit from some of the Gilber}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377  and Sullivan, different times, different - plays. Others -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh well I think I always recited
, I can't sing a note. As I think is obvious from my voice. But - I - generally - that was what I had to do. And sometimes father wanted me to do things that - at a later date I could understand the point of them but I didn't at that time. Various types o
f verses you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was it all planned out beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh no. No, you planned yourselves, each family planned what they were going to do, and one or two - one aunt was quite good at accompanying all the singers. Which was quite a help. Then various cousins could play. Some played a violin and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What musical instruments did you have in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Just a piano, but then that was also a thing for gathering people - together. For singing. Whether you could sing much or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you actually sing as a family then, in the evenings perhaps?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 A bit more with mother - than with dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of things would you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh mostly the - the student songs, and the old Scots songs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, cards a bit. Draughts upon occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Not chess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. Mother, strangely enough, in h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 er later years began - took up }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 chess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 But you didn't have that as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ah, there were always quite a lot of books, father had been rather good at collecting books. And - very good - at getting you anything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was there a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, but in these days the - public libraries were rather shunned, because some of them were - some of the bo
oks were not - like today at all. Not overclean. But there attain - down at Skelmerley there was an excellent library, and from my early teens I thought I had struck a goldmine when I got there. And the librarian, I had great friends with and he used to -
 let me know what he had. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He would keep the good ones for you when you came down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. But - there again you've to remember that - like what we call paperbacks now - were - edited in hard covers, red covers, ever so many authors, at sixpence
 a time. And very often - men travelling up and down would buy these. You see. And I was lucky that there was - one or two people, friends of my father's who'd pass them on to me. I'm sorry I've passed many of them on, and have them now. At one point I ha
d a whole collection of O'Henry's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 But there was always plenty to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about magazines and newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Newspapers yes. Very few magazines except Chambers Journal, in which there were some very good stories. And articles.
 A fairly well known people, that came in once a month. And - and he used to watch for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 As a family did you read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You said you read to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, that - that was quite a thing, my mother rather liked
 that. Get a good book and - very often it was - rather Jean who was so young and - mother and I, mother would read a chapter and - I would - be sewing or knitting and then - we would - take it turn about. But in fact that's how I - I was so keen on readi
ng. It wasn't - considered right - to have your hands idle. Therefore, I learned to read and knit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was it considered you were wasting your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. A little bit - not so much with my parents. Various other relatives were of that opinion, and didn't h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 sitate to voice their opinion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Do you remember any funerals in the family when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. I was sixteen when my grand - mother died. Or fifteen, and - a couple of years later - grand - father, my grandfather died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Would you be too young to go to the funeral then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, it was - wasn't considered - right. Possibly had it been a parent that might have been different. One or two aunts died but only the parents attended the funerals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was it the done thing in your family for the women to go to the funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
They only went to the house, they didn't attend the actual funeral, but they went to the house where, if it was a relative, the - there would be a service in the house. Before going. Yes. And then - the usual man
ner - in - as in the old days, of the people all returning to the house. After the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about mourning, did you have to wear mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. The only - all I can remember was, a - a very nice outfit it was - getting - one - the - of the fi
rst - costumes made, it actually was a three - quarter fitted coat and skirt in grey, when my grandfather died. I remember that quite clearly, because it was very well made - made by my father's tailor, which meant that it lasted for years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Grey was considered half mourning or something wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, it was, but mother - did not like to see children - I mean I was by that time as I say I was sixteen, it was - a - a silver grey, it was anything - it wasn't at all like mourning, and - my - mothe
r always felt that - it's how you feel, not what you wear that matters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours and friends and relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Sometimes. The - relatives yes, but very often there, there would be a family, and the children went o
ff on their own. They didn't sit with the grown ups, only occasionally. Were you taken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your mother go out visiting quite a bit in the afternoons or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 A fair bit. Not - a tremendous lot, but you see - all the ladies had their own particul
ar at home day, once a month. Where their friends came. I can still remember - mother's was the first Wednesday of the month. And all her friends came, and many of them there were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well you see, she was fortunate i
n this, that many of them had been her old school friends. And all her sisters, and they'd all been friendly together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And they all lived fairly near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well - not so near latterly, but they all came, and the same people - that went down in crowds
 to mothers to the Skelmerley house - for the various weekends, that was the way they had their outings. And then my father - would sometimes take us, I've seen him - have as many as eight or nine ladies that he took with them to the theatre. Because many
 of them had not married. You see? And in each case there was maybe several sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And he took the lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. My mother referred to them as the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did they ever go out say for a dinner in the evening to friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh quite a lot. Quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 They went out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, and also - my father - was connected with various - things where there were - dinners. That they had quite a lot of outings. He was a Deacon of the Weavers, through my grandfather's side. The Trades House. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It's like the Merchants in Edinburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Well there was also the Clydesdale Merchants. And the - the Eastern Merchants. Various functions - that he was connected with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So he would be out quite a few evenings then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. In fact in his last - weeks of his life - there wasn't a night he was in. That - that partly - was - being without mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 After he was on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. But - but the - he was attached to quite a number of things, but - there were social - outings, as well as - visiting friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about Saturdays, when you weren't at school, what would you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Well, Saturday morning, you certainly had to lend a hand. Incidentally, as you got older, whether there was a girl in the kitchen or not - y
ou took it in turns to dry dishes, because of the number. Mother never objected to you having friends but she felt that - any girl in the kitchen who had helped with the preparing, left with all the dishes - and then drying, it wasn't fair. And Saturday m
o
rning - somebody was always there to lend a hand with that after you had straightened your bedroom. Thereafter you went to the baths, mostly. And came home lunch time, which of course as I said, was dinner, and father would be there. Father and mother - a
n
d the family - when young, all set forth then for - my grandfather's, as you got older the younger members went and latterly, you were left to look after the young ones and father and mother went on their own. As the old people was getting older and - it 
was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It would be a bit much to have a lot of children round them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Though there was - there was plenty of time to let them - loose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about Sundays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, Sundays, you were - you went to church in the morning for the eleven o'clock service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ordinary church of Scotland was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. Congregational. You - then - had - a light meal then, because mother hadn't gone out in the morning, she went with father again to the afternoon service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have two or three services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Two. The two services, except for special occasions when they had three, it was the evening service as well. We went as a family with father in the morning, and mother went with father in the afternoon, we then - went to Sunday school, which - b
egan after the second service. In the hall. In the church. Yes. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It was a way of letting the parents got to the church while the children were taken care of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, it followed - afterwards. Yes. Then you had - a main meal when you came h
ome - from - Sunday school, 'cos quite often - there was really only time for - coffee and - a - sort of sandwich thing in the middle of the day or coffee and cheese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It would be quite late before you got your dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, really I would - 
I would think it would be just - half past four. So it - it - it sort of took the place of tea, things-were reversed. As it were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about your clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh special clothes - special clothes for Sunday. You put them on for the church, you took them off when you came in. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What did you put on then after you'd taken your Sunday clothes off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh a comfortable dress. We weren't held down the way some people were, some people would not allow any book except the Bible in - op
ened in the house on Sunday. No, we could do anything that didn't disturb other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were allowed to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, any game we liked that didn't disturb other people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You went to Sunday school, did you ever have any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh yes, I hated them. I wasn't - that's my fault, I wasn't over fond of crowds. I didn't like tea as we'd all been brought up on milk. And tea with sugar in it was also that was provided. Buns - that I had never met up with at home. Didn't - appe
al. But the fault was mine. I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have to go to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. It was the thing to go. In any case I wasn't athletic and I wasn't very good at run races.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you have Sunday school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 soirees as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ah yes, that was more fu
n. There again - you did turns. And - but once again I couldn't drink the tea, and when it came near the middle of the first world war I can remember mother saying, you girls'll need to learn to drink tea because you can't ask for milk. People haven't got
 it. You'll need to take tea like me, with milk but no sugar. So we did take it that way, 'til I was about sixteen, and going down to Skelmerley, you've to remember milk wasn't in bottles then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 But you would have it delivered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Out of a churn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
That's right. But there wouldn't have been any milk till the morning and I'd been asked to - fill a bottle with milk. I did, I sterilized the bottle but I'd - forgotten to - to watch \{ILLEGIBLE\} the cork and come from, it had come from a peppe
rmint bottle. And the poor people who tried to drink that tea never took milk in their tea again. So I take it now minus milk and sugar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 When you went to Skelmerley for weekends what about church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Sometimes - sometimes yes, not always. The 
minister - was rather a difficult man, who - talking in a normal voice would suddenly shout, I suppose to wake his congregation. But - we found it rather tiring. So - we didn't always attend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were there any other clubs or organisations run by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh yes. There again you met the same people. They - today I am still friendly with quite a few who were in the Sunday school class, they - there was - the - the Band of Hope, there were the Crusaders, which -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What were Crusaders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Crusaders were supposed to be temperance people, there was a little badge one got and you had to swear - never to take - alcohol, but at that time half the time you didn't really realize what it was because - you didn't see it in your own
 house. And that - there again, if anybody was having a drink it was rather secret. It wasn't - brought forth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Like New Year and Christmas and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, very very little. Very very little. I think the grown ups very often had a drink when they 
had chased the younger people away to something else. But you certainly never saw it. Though I knew where - a bottle of sherry, whisky and brandy was kept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 But you never actually saw them being used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, in fact - we were - quite grown up almost
 when - my father - who could make his own toddy in his bedroom, though he was a very - abstemious man - had said to one of my sisters, would you give me a pan with a little water, and I want some sugar, and she said would you hand me the glass and I'll b
ring you the toddy when it's ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What did he have to say then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
He had nothing to say, so from then on he didn't bother so much. And of course when he got sons-in-law, they made a great joke of this business of do you want to wash your hands when it was really do you want a whisky and soda?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Father. Father did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And if he wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What about prayers at night, did you say prayers when you went to bed at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh yes. But - family prayers was a thing that weren't - done in our house though they were in my grandfather's. Definitely there was family prayers always - if you were in my grandfather's house. Not with us except when a certain elder came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were the Elders fairly regular in their visits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Fairly. Oh - children of course - remember - things - because they're out of the usual. And I can remember - the old fashioned - dining room table cloth, with the fringes that - che
nille table cloth that came right down to the - floor. And four little girls who had just had their bath, all hiding below there when they heard the voice of - a man coming in, and mother trying to - get - to speak politely and get him away before bursts 
o
f laughter came from below the table. Oh we would have come through probably to dry our hair, 'cos very often that would be when - hair was washed you see, you - you - your - your bath and your hair washed, I think it would be a Friday. And you would come
 through to dry it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You would all have long hair would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Longish, until it came to my youngest sister. And then she had short hair because by that time short hair was coming in for grown ups.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Was your father interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, quite a bit. Quite a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of views did he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I would say he leaned more towards a - Liberal. But - when they - were - falling into disfavour he certainly wasn't Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What about mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I think mother d
idn't worry very much, she was more interested in peoples characters than politics, more interested in individuals. People - people - people -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She would vote for the man rather than the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh my - no, I rather think though she wasn't inclined to follow my father in everything, I think she held fairly similar views.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Do you remember your father voting in an election, a general election, before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes, I can remember that because - there used to be a battle royal between the sc
hools. And you either wore a red or a blue rosette, as to whether you were Liberal or - Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Even in the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. The children in the schools, well there was the primary school and the senior school. And - one was down one hill and
 one down the other. And there came on the election day, I presume we must have had a holiday that day, a battle royal between - whether those with the blue b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 adges and those with the red ba}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 tes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Do you think you understood what it was all about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
No, I don't think we really did, but I still can picture the hoards of children coming running up - to meet, which happened to be just about the corner of our drive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Talking about battles like that, did you have any problems about religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh w
ell - they did - there did - there - you see - Catholics were - really looked down on. That is true. But the truth was, you knew very few of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Weren't there many in - your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, very very few. As a matter of fact I can only remember two 
families. Mrs Small went on to say after the recording had finished that it wasn't until she went to art college when she was about seventeen that she realized just how comfortable her family was as far as money was concerned. Money was never spoken about
 
in their house. As a child she got first a penny a week pocket money and then it went up to tuppence and then up to a shilling as things got more expensive she said. And when she started travelling to school in the centre of Glasgow she got five shillings
 
a week, which had to cover her bus fares as well. She used to walk home and save a ha'penny on the tram. It was only when she started at art college that she realized that other people were not in the same position as she was financially. She mentioned to
w
 of the girls in her class that at art college, one who was the daughter of a miner, a very talented girl who really had to struggle to make her way through college and the other one came from Greenock I think and was in similar circumstances. A lot of th
e
 girls at art college at that time were just putting off time until they could get themselves a husband. This was considered something that they could do when they didn't have to go out to work, but didn't want to stay at home doing nothing. Mrs Small rem
a
rked that it had been something to be wondered at that she had said definitely that she wanted to teach art, because it appeared that she didn't have to go out to work, it was just because she wanted to do it herself that she went ahead and did this. I di
d
n't ask any questions about Mrs Small's marriage. Her daughter is a friend of mine as I told you and her father had vanished from the scene completely, and it's a very sore subject with the daughter and - I've never been able to find out exactly what happ
e
ned to the marriage, but when Mrs Small's daughter was quite small they went back to live with the grandfather, Mr Folds, and father hasn't been seen or heard of since. The daughter doesn't even know whether he's alive at the moment or not, but the interv
i
ew was conducted on the assumption that no questions would be asked in that region. I didn't ask any questions either about her sisters getting on well together, because I know from personal experience that Mrs Small does not get on well at all with her o
l
der sister, Frances. They're still at daggers drawn in fact and they hardly speak to each other, but she seemed to get on very well with her other sisters in particular the youngest one, who the whole family seems to be rather proud of. She is an elocutio
n
 teacher in Glasgow to this day, and very often has parts on radio and television plays, playing Scots parts. The oldest sister didn't work at all. The mother of the family took ill when the oldest sister was about seventeen and Mrs Small was about fiftee
n
. And the oldest sister left school and by the time her mother was fit again, it was too late to do anything more about schooling and she got married just as mother was recovering. One of the younger sisters, Bell, went in for nursing, but found it too mu
c
h of a strain on her health and had to give up. Mrs Small was a bit shy of talking of her mother's illness, she didn't want any of this written down but - she said that mother contracted a virus infection during the first world war while she was doing som
e
 social work for troops. I don't know if they were returned wounded, something of that sort. She contracted this virus and was in a coma for something like six months, but she recovered eventually and was more or less hail and hearty for the next twenty y
e
ars until she died. Mrs Small gave up school to help and she and the older sister Frances took over the running of the house while their mother was unconscious. She said that it was good experience for them, but they made an awful lot of mistakes, even wi
t
h the help of the Maggie, the housemaid. She reckons that she ran more messages during that period because of things which had been forgotten to be ordered from the shops than ever she did before. It was in fact unusual for them to go shopping at all, as 
t
he tradesmen in this district where they lived called round every morning and collected orders for groceries and so on and goods were delivered later on. There was no need to go to the shops at all. Mrs Small's father, although he wasn't actively involved
 in politics in Glasgow, appears to have had something of a social conscience, because she mentioned later that he was involved in a special committee of enquiry into housing conditions in Glasgow which had to report to Lord North in London, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about school, when did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I was six before I started school. Partly because of the illness of the - sister younger t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 han me, we went to stay in Mill}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 port for six months. But - you started - at that time I think quite a lot of people did not start just on five. And that was in -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You didn't go to any nursery school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No. It was - considered the thing for your mother to teach you - hand work before you went to the school. You - in fact -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were lucky because you had a mother that could do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, but as a matter of fact one of the worst things at that time that you could say against a girl in Scotland was she was handless.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That's still a phrase that's used today isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. But - this was the idea. You
 learnt from your mother by helping her, how to bake, how to sew, how to knit. And how to do various little jobs about the house like dusting and - so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 The essentials?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. You learnt really without being aware of it. Possib - possibly y
ou were - stoning the raisins and - for the - a pudding and told to whistle while you - did it so that you didn't eat too many. And - you learnt what went into the pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Just by watching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. You weren't even aware you were learning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So you started school at six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Which school was it you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 The local school, Alexandra Parade. And I stayed there 'til I would be eleven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That was the primary education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. And then I moved into town. To the Girls
 High School. Once I was travelling for a year my younger sisters then went joining the primary of the girls high school, since they had someone to travel with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your older sister go there too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. She went to Whitehill School, which was the 
senior secondary school. For the district. It originally opened at what was called the third standard. And my mother actually attended there right at the beginning of that school. For a little - because they had moved in from Busby. You see? My grandfathe
r had taken over the mill in Bridgston as I told you. So they had moved then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Why didn't you go there as well then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, my cousins and friends were going in to town. So I - went where they went. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 When you were at the primary school you would be able to come home for your - dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What happened when you went to the High School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, at that time your - first senior year, you only had one late day. You stopped at - I think it was - either half past twelve o
r quarter to one. But then you had a lot of homework. Yes, you could wait in school for the prep class - or go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So you could go home and have dinner at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, and then the following year perhaps you had two late days, then three la
te days, by the time you were in - I think by the time you were in third year you just had one early day. But - a lot was - expected of the pupils in homework. Rather good I think because it taught you to work on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 This is what they say is lacking nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. Yes. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377  another}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
thing that I think was very good was in the High School the headmistress not only vetted the timetable, she vetted the timetable of homework, and she knew exactly what was expected of you - on a given night
. Each teacher could only give out so many exercises in the week. And these had to be done. And - they had to be well done, because the marks of these - were read out by the headmistress in front of your class every week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That could be quite shattering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
It was. Very often for me, I wasn't very clever. English and art were my subjects mainly. I could pass in other things but - not - not at all outstanding. Rather unfortunate as I'd cousins a head of me who were brilliant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And you were expected to follow in the family tradition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did the girls take it out on people who weren't bright?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh no. Oh no, in fact rather the reverse. If you were known to be a swot for instance - that wasn't really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were looked down on for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, I would say so. But you see there were - the - classes that were taking classical languages, the classes that were taking modern languages, but you could still be in a - an A of either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Wasn't there anything toward the scientific side at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes, though I don't think it was stressed half as much as it is now because it didn't have as much bearing on life as it was lived.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 To go back to your primary school, did you go a whole day to begin with or did you have a half day there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I think I'm right in saying it was 'til three o'clock - for so long and then 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How far away was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh - two or three minutes - from the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 So you left at five to nine did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. And severe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 ly deal with if you were late.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What were the teachers like in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Some of them - were quite - good, others were - bullies. Specially men teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You had men teachers in the primary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. At that time there were quite a few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What age would you start having men teachers, was it the higher classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well - I think so, I think - from about - ten. Nine or ten you had - male teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did the teachers emphasise certain things in life, like manners and punctuality and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Not much in the elementary school. Punctuality yes. For the other things no. Some of the women were rather better on that. But - quite different when you got to senior school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What was the difference then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Behaviour and manners a must.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did they have any rules that you would consider silly today, about manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Not on manners, but - we were rather a boisterous family, and - from the word go I seemed to get in trouble with the headmistress for boisterous behaviour but I'd never had any difficulty with my other teachers. I was extremely lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you tend to rush about in corridors or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh, that was completely forbidden. No - it was a very small playground. And I think each one of 
our family got in trouble for being boisterous in the same - playground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about your way of speaking, did they try to influence your accent, either in primary or the secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, in - in secondary - most people spoke very much - al
ike, you know - their - accent was similar. They came from similar backgrounds and their accent was similar.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It was a fee paying school wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That you had better class children going to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Most of them were from similar
 backgrounds. Many of them went on to university. It was still - quite in order for those who weren't able for that just to stay at home when they'd finished school. Not to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 They didn't have to go out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about punishments in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 In the elementary they had corporal punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 With a strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. Not in senior school at all. No. You got - a bad mark. I can recollect in my first report - my father reading it out, he said, Agnes is reported for a bre
ach of school regulations. What is this? I said, I was talking in class. Father said, they've only got it down once, are they hard of hearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It's almost like the army isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes, well you see that was the aspect of the headmistress. Sh
e was a very clever woman, she was very strict - but, she had very little understanding of children as children. Fortunately the teachers weren't - like that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You got on quite well with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh very well yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were they all women in the High School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Except the science master, there had been one or two but you see the war had taken them all away. And - I just - remember one who left just as I went, and another - remained, he was elderly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What about the punishment in the primary school, did the girls and boys get the same sort of punishment?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No difference was made at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No difference. More especially I would say with the men teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 They were fairer than the women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. They were much - much more inclined to use a strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of things did they get the strap for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Getting something wrong. Which I think is terrible. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Your parents were very interested in what you did at school were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes, very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Nowadays you have open days at school and the parents can go and talk to the teachers and so on, was it like that in your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No. Later in the senior school when the headmistress changed - things changed - there. My younger sister was rat
her better off, I think, on that score. I knew - the lady who became - headmistress, she had been my French teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 A bit more liberal minded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, she was a married woman who had children. She was a widow. She was a widow. She had - she had ha
d children, she was excellent with children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She would know how their minds worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Did you find that in either of the schools the teacher singled out any children for special treatment, did you have teachers pets or did the teachers seem to pick on anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No, I don't recollect much of that at all. It would definite - that would definitely have been frowned on by the headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She wouldn't have liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What age were you when you finished school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
I was sixteen, because of mother's illness I left then and having discovered I left early that term - in fourth year. I left early that term because of mother - and then - I - found out that I could go to the art school and spending an extra year there
 - go right though the course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You could make up what you had lost at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That would suit you better really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes, much better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 If it hadn't been for your mother's illness you would probably have stayed on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I expect so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Until you were seventeen or eighteen, how long were you in art school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That's a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Instead of four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And you were saying you had your trip - to Paris?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, that was just about my final year
, or second - last year, I can't quite recollect. But it was - a great opportunity you know, I saw such a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 It would finish off your education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Mm hm. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 When your mother was ill did your older sister stay at home to look after the house as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Do you remember seeing a policeman round about where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. Yes, there was a - policeman always there, we had a very rude nickname for him. As he was very stout.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Were you quite friendly with him, you weren't frightened of him as a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Well - yes and no, you certainly wouldn't get up to any mischief. But then if you had your parents would have dealt with you, you just were not allowed to misbehave. And that - was not just in - your own family. Anyb
ody who got the name of misbehaving was somewhat shunned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You wouldn't be invited into other peoples houses with their children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Your parents didn't have to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You didn't have any families like that round about you were in contact with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
I remember once - hearing a girl say - that because - they - I was in elementary school at this time, because the boys had got new kilts they weren't going for a holiday. I couldn't see the connection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You had your holiday every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. But I could recollect - there were some of course in the class who wouldn't have a great deal. I can remember - some were talking about what their father's made, and of course I went home and asked and mother j
ust - without blinking an eyelid just said, fifteen shillings a week. And I went back to the school and reported that. How he could have kept us all on that I just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 But as long as you got an answer you were quite happy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. Just as - one 
child that wore fancy frilly - underwear and I asked to get on my dancing - things, mother said, oh you see, I think that girl's mother will only have one. I have five. So I think I would prefer in the winter that you wear your navy things and in the summ
e
r your summer ones. Again mother was ahead of her time because in making our summer clothes, your - pants were made like the shorts of today. In the material that your dress was made of, so that when you went to the coast, and you remember you were there 
for a couple of months, you put your dress inside the pants if you were going paddling, and you looked all of a piece, instead of a bit of a mess.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I think it's her artistic eye coming out again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. She - she really was ahead of her time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You mentioned the dancing classes that you went to, can you tell me a bit about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, well up 'til - I would be - about - nine I think - or ten, you went to a very select dancing class, where even - for the lessons the boys had to wear white 
gloves. And there you learnt - oh - special dances - like - Highland dance, Spanish dance - various types of dancing and of course waltzing, Lancers, Quadrilles, Eightsome, but all done in the correct fashion. No - noisy boisterous swinging, that came lat
er when you went on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How did that suit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ah well, that was fun because - a lot of the bigger boys were very kindly to the younger girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 They looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. It was quite different type of dancing that I went to - once I had gone to senior school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of age would be when you went out to dances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Oh - that would be - between fifteen and sixteen. Sixteen I would say. But then you see there weren't public dance halls. And - people gave private dances, you were invited to these.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You say your father went out to dinners and so on connected with his various offices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did you they have dances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 When we were older we attended dances connected - once we had frown up, from eighteen - nineteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You were considered grown up at eighteen were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Well, yes, you were considered you should be able to - behave, and there were dinners connected with the various - societies that father - was in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You said that you had elocution lessons too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, that was in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 Athenaeum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
In Glasgow - in Glasgow. It is now where the - the drama college is although I believe recently they've moved to another building. But it was in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 Athenaeum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377  in Buchanan Street, and you went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And it was purely elocution?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes, and drama, and you took part in various plays - through out the season. Sometimes Shakespeare and sometimes Dickens, sometimes more modern -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You actually gave performances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Oh yes. For the public, they - they had quite a nice little theatre in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 
Athenaeum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You started that when you were quite young did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, I would be about - nine when I began there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That would be quite good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, it was very good. I enjoy
ed it thoroughly. Memorizing things was no difficulty. In fact I think that rather held me back in some of the things I had to learn, because - you learnt by - rote - without worrying overmuch about - solving the problem.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did your young sisters start off at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 Athenaeum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377  as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ah - no. No. My - the others didn't go, they went to music. I had been sent to music but I was no good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 That was for piano lessons was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Then my youngest sister of course - elocution was what she studie
d, but she studied with a private teacher and then went to London to be trained. At the - at the Slade - the Slade Drama School in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about the people in your circle in the area where you lived, who would you say were the most important peopl
e then? What sort of place did the minister have in your society?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Well you see - first of all when I was young, the sen - the minister - they had been a friend of my mother's since she was a girl and she was - his daughters were my mother's - friends. So that we were very familiar with the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 He was a personal friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. Then - the other minister, the next minister who came - was also a friend, his sister was - quite a regular caller - at mother's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 How about doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Ther
e again, the doctor - that had come when we were born was the same doctor - who was still attending us when we were grown up. Yes, he also - he was also a friend, and - his wife and daughter - we knew, his daughter came to school with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Really the people round about were much of the same social class, there was no one up above or down below?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. Well - well in the surrounding area, but you see the suburbs at that time were almost like villages, in that so many of the parents knew one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 In your area do you think it was possible for people to move up the social scale or down the social scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 I don't think we ever paid the slightest attention to that so it didn't register. We - we met - in - as I've said - in Sabbath school, at 
the baths - and there there would be quite a mixture, though it didn't register with us because - money was never mentioned. Behaviour was much more important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You might have got people who had made some money and moved into your district but didn't h
ave the same sort of behaviour pattern as you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
I can't recollect any like that. The bit was - by the time we had more or less grown up a lot of people had moved either to Burnside or Givnock, where I now am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What sort of attitude would you have towards Maggie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. But no servant in our house was ever treated other than with the greatest kindness and consideration, and that was their word, not mine. Recently -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 She stayed with you a long time didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes, recently though 
she is dead now, recently my youngest sister was in Rosemarkey where she came from, and - enquired - and - relatives said, oh, she always spoke of your mother and of her kindness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And how did you children get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Well, if she was in - if - if she was in charge she had authority. If mother wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 You had to do what she said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
Yes. Yes. And later - other maids, we had one or two that didn't stay long - then we had one that was there a - long time. And moved with us when we moved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Did she just call you by your first name as your mother would do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Until we were grown up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 What did she call you after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Miss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13107468 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 And your first name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9395681 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 Yes. Yes. But - while we were young always just by your name. Af
ter finishing the recording Mrs Small and I were chatting and I asked about boys. Whether going to a girls school she had found that there were many boys in her circle, and she said, yes, there were lots of boys in the families round about, they were used
 to playing with them and they met them at parties and so on. Apart from that although she went to a girls school all the boys from the district trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 led in the tram at the same time to their schools in the mornings and back at night. She recalled the occa
sion of the Armistice in 1918 when the boys from the High School in Glasgow and from Kelvinside Academy had all marched en masse to the High School for girls and the headmistress had been absolutely shattered that the scenes outside where the boys, about 
s
eventeen eighteen year olds were dancing with the girls, and great singing and carrying on, and she had addressed the school afterwards and said that she was disgusted that they should have been consorting with boys, as if they were things that crawled ou
t
 of the woodwork. Mrs Small also mentioned the fact that from the age of about fifteen or sixteen the girls in the family were allowed to go down to the Skelmerley house for weekends with their friends, completely on their own without supervision. She rec
k
oned that it was good training for them in cooking for themselves and doing their own housekeeping, although she did that admit that it was a case of ordering what you required from the tradesmen who delivered it and father was sent the bill. Talking of t
h
is reminded her of the occasion when she herself was about sixteen, and father had got a bill for materials for summer dresses for the mother and the five girls. And he was taken back when the bill for the material and not for the making up came to over a
 
hundred pounds. Whereupon he reckoned it was time that the older girls had a dress allowance, which they had to spin out themselves, which made them a bit more careful. Mrs Small also told me of the time when she was about nineteen, she was taken to Paris
h
 for something like three months by two elderly gentlemen who were friends of the family, and who chaperoned her very carefully when she was in Paris. She found this very useful in her education as far as art was concerned. But her sisters were very disap
p
ointed when she came home from Paris in exactly the same clothes as she went away, she hadn't looked at clothes at all. After leaving art college she got a job teaching art and at that time moved from her own home into digs for some time. During the time 
t
hat she was working as an art teacher she returned to live with her father after her mother had died and lived in the same house until her father died when she moved out and got a house of her own. At a later meeting Mrs Small was recalling an item of ent
e
rtainment in the family which she had forgotten about. This was called a parlour full she thinks. It was a gadget which was attached to the telephone, there were two speakers, one on either side of the fireplace in their lounge or sitting room, and by cal
l
ing up the music halls in Glasgow on the telephone, you could have the show which was on in the music hall could be reproduced over the loudspeakers on either side of the fireplace. She doesn't remember hearing very much herself, because she reckons that 
m
other and father listened after the children were away to bed at night, but she had often wondered how her mother knew all the words of the music hall songs and thinks that this must have been where she heard them. Apparently the arrangement was topped af
ter a fairly short time because the music halls found that they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7625930\charrsid5124377 listing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485353\charrsid5124377 
 customers on a wet night instead of people going out to the music hall they just sat at home and listened on their private telephone to the show that was being performed. At this m
eeting this afternoon I also asked Mrs Small about the maid again. About where she slept and as I thought she slept in the kitchen. In a bed recess - in the kitchen.
